From 86f9224826d50c5e21a8e84e4881b9c23435c6b9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Aaron Paterson <apaterson@pm.me>
Date: Mon, 16 Mar 2026 22:28:29 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] refs: add helper backend for external ref storage

Introduce REF_STORAGE_FORMAT_HELPER, a new ref storage backend that
delegates ref operations to an external process. This follows the
same pattern as the ODB helper backend (odb/source-helper.c) and
transport helpers (git-remote-*).

The helper binary is discovered as "git-ref-<name>" in PATH. It is
invoked with the gitdir path as its sole argument and communicates
via a line-based protocol on stdin/stdout:

  capabilities -> list supported commands
  read <refname> -> oid, symref target, or "missing"
  list [prefix] -> refname + oid/symref per line, blank terminates
  transaction-begin -> ok
  transaction-update/create/delete/create-symref -> ok
  transaction-prepare -> ok/error
  transaction-finish -> ok/error
  transaction-abort -> ok
  create -> ok/error (initialize storage)

Configuration uses the same URI format as existing ref storage:

  [extensions]
    refStorage = helper://sqlite

This sets ref_storage_format to REF_STORAGE_FORMAT_HELPER with
"sqlite" as the payload, causing git to spawn "git-ref-sqlite" and
pass all ref operations through it.

Together with the ODB helper backend, this enables testing complete
alternative storage backends (like sqlite-git) without compiling
them into git.

Reflog operations return success without storing, as the helper
protocol does not yet include reflog commands. This matches the
behavior of a backend that does not maintain reflogs.

Include an integration test (t0621) that exercises ref creation,
reading, and listing through a shell-based test helper.

Signed-off-by: Aaron Willoughby <aaron@omniband.org>
